The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Calcutta, April 5 : The Hindustan Motors management has asked for a commitment from unions that violence at its Uttarpara plant will be stopped before talks scheduled on April 8.

 The management has also taken on lease 50 apartments in Calcutta for its staff.

 Calcutta: A former secretary of the land and land reforms department, Debabrata Bandyopadhyay, has moved the high court challenging the process adopted to acquire land in Singur for the Tata Motors unit.




